'''Vanessa Taylor''' is an American scriptwriter and producer. She has written several episodes of ''[[wikipedia:Alias (TV series)|Alias]]'' and ''[[wikipedia:Everwood (TV series)|Everwood]]''. She was a writer and producer for ''[[wikipedia:Tell Me You Love Me|Tell Me You Love Me]]''.

On ''[[Game of Thrones]],'' Taylor is a co-executive producer&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.deadline.com/2011/09/movie-lit-agent-jumping-to-icm-from-uta/ Deadline]&lt;/ref&gt; and scriptwriter, penning two episodes of the [[Season 2|second season]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/One_More_Season_2_Writer/ Westeros.org]&lt;/ref&gt; and one of the [[Season 3|third]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.westeros.org/GoT/News/Entry/HBO_Releases_Season_3_Episode_Writers_and_Directors Westeros.org]]&lt;/ref&gt;

Taylor left working on ''Game of Thrones'' after Season 3, to work on the film adaptation of the young adult novel ''Divergent'' (2014).  It is unknown if she will return.
